#. <section class="sutta" id="an4.52"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.52:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.52:0.2"
msgid "6. Puññābhisandavagga"
msgstr "6. Overflowing Merit"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.52:0.3"
msgid "52. Dutiyapuññābhisandasutta"
msgstr "52. Overflowing Merit (2nd)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an4.52:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puññābhisandā kusalābhisandā sukhassāhārā sovaggikā "
"sukhavipākā saggasaṃvattanikā iṭṭhāya kantāya manāpāya hitāya sukhāya "
"saṃvattanti."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, there are these four kinds of overflowing merit, overflowing "
"goodness. They nurture happiness and are conducive to heaven, ripening in "
"happiness and leading to heaven. They lead to what is likable, desirable, "
"agreeable, to welfare and happiness."

msgctxt "an4.52:1.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "an4.52:1.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti:"
msgstr "When a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Buddha:"

msgctxt "an4.52:1.4"
msgid ""
"‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū "
"anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in "
"knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those "
"who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’"

msgctxt "an4.52:1.5"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamo puññābhisando kusalābhisando sukhassāhāro sovaggiko "
"sukhavipāko saggasaṃvattaniko iṭṭhāya kantāya manāpāya hitāya sukhāya "
"saṃvattati."
msgstr "This is the first kind of overflowing merit …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an4.52:2.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako dhamme aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti:"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the teaching:"

msgctxt "an4.52:2.2"
msgid ""
"‘svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo sandiṭṭhiko akāliko ehipassiko opaneyyiko "
"paccattaṃ veditabbo viññūhī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘The teaching is well explained by the Buddha—realizable in this very life, "
"immediately effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible "
"people can know it for themselves.’"

msgctxt "an4.52:2.3"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyo puññābhisando kusalābhisando sukhassāhāro sovaggiko "
"sukhavipāko saggasaṃvattaniko iṭṭhāya kantāya manāpāya hitāya sukhāya "
"saṃvattati."
msgstr "This is the second kind of overflowing merit …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an4.52:3.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako saṅghe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti:"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Saṅgha:"

msgctxt "an4.52:3.2"
msgid ""
"‘suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho, ujuppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho, "
"ñāyappaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho, sāmīcippaṭipanno bhagavato "
"sāvakasaṅgho, yadidaṃ cattāri purisayugāni aṭṭha purisapuggalā, esa "
"bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho āhuneyyo pāhuneyyo dakkhiṇeyyo añjalikaraṇīyo "
"anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘The Saṅgha of the Buddha’s disciples is practicing the way that’s good, "
"straightforward, methodical, and proper. It consists of the four pairs, the "
"eight individuals. This is the Saṅgha of the Buddha’s disciples that is "
"worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of "
"a teacher’s offering, worthy of greeting with joined palms, and is the "
"supreme field of merit for the world.’"

msgctxt "an4.52:3.3"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyo puññābhisando kusalābhisando sukhassāhāro sovaggiko "
"sukhavipāko saggasaṃvattaniko iṭṭhāya kantāya manāpāya hitāya sukhāya "
"saṃvattati."
msgstr "This is the third kind of overflowing merit …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.57"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an4.52:4.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato hoti "
"akhaṇḍehi acchiddehi asabalehi akammāsehi bhujissehi viññuppasatthehi "
"aparāmaṭṭhehi samādhisaṃvattanikehi."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a noble disciple’s ethical conduct is loved by the noble ones, "
"unbroken, impeccable, spotless, and unmarred, liberating, praised by "
"sensible people, not mistaken, and leading to immersion."

msgctxt "an4.52:4.2"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, catuttho puññābhisando kusalābhisando sukhassāhāro "
"sovaggiko sukhavipāko saggasaṃvattaniko iṭṭhāya kantāya manāpāya hitāya "
"sukhāya saṃvattati."
msgstr "This is the fourth kind of overflowing merit …"

msgctxt "an4.52:4.3"
msgid ""
"Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puññābhisandā kusalābhisandā sukhassāhārā "
"sovaggikā sukhavipākā saggasaṃvattanikā iṭṭhāya kantāya manāpāya hitāya "
"sukhāya saṃvattantīti."
msgstr ""
"These are the four kinds of overflowing merit, overflowing goodness. They "
"nurture happiness and are conducive to heaven, ripening in happiness and "
"leading to heaven. They lead to what is likable, desirable, agreeable, to "
"welfare and happiness."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an4.52:5.1"
msgid "Yassa saddhā tathāgate,"
msgstr "Whoever has faith in the Realized One,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.52:5.2"
msgid "acalā suppatiṭṭhitā;"
msgstr "unwavering and well grounded;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.52:5.3"
msgid "Sīlañca yassa kalyāṇaṃ,"
msgstr "whose ethical conduct is good,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.52:5.4"
msgid "ariyakantaṃ pasaṃsitaṃ."
msgstr "praised and loved by the noble ones;"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an4.52:6.1"
msgid "Saṅghe pasādo yassatthi,"
msgstr "who has confidence in the Saṅgha,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.52:6.2"
msgid "ujubhūtañca dassanaṃ;"
msgstr "and correct view:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.52:6.3"
msgid "Adaliddoti taṃ āhu,"
msgstr "they’re said to be prosperous,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.52:6.4"
msgid "amoghaṃ tassa jīvitaṃ."
msgstr "their life is not in vain."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an4.52:7.1"
msgid "Tasmā saddhañca sīlañca,"
msgstr "So let the wise devote themselves"

# This line is of course displaced. Like BB, I render buddhanasasana as singular, despite that fact that the received form is plural. I assume the original reading is anusasana. It seems to me incongruous that one should be asked to “remember the instruction of (all) the Buddhas”.
#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.52:7.2"
msgid "pasādaṃ dhammadassanaṃ;"
msgstr "to faith, ethical behaviour,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.52:7.3"
msgid "Anuyuñjetha medhāvī,"
msgstr "confidence, and insight into the teaching,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.52:7.4"
msgid "saraṃ buddhāna sāsanan”ti."
msgstr "remembering the instructions of the Buddhas."

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.52:7.5"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
